<section class="vc-feat" id="doctrine">
  <div class="vc-feat-orn vc-orn-rule reveal"><span class="mk">§</span></div>
  <div class="vc-feat-rubric reveal">A Coalition of the Willing</div>
  <h2 class="vc-feat-h reveal">Two missions, <em>one lineage.</em></h2>
  <div class="vc-feat-cols reveal">
    <div class="vc-feat-col">
      <h3><span class="roman">I.</span>The Mission of Record</h3>
      <p class="drop">E5 Enclave is a lineage-led think tank convening a Coalition of the Willing to build the institutions, evidence systems, collaborative platforms, and community projects needed to advance the future of <em>the lineage</em>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-feat-col">
      <h3><span class="roman">II.</span>The Public Mission</h3>
      <p class="drop">From {{ site.established.city }} to the nation, E5 builds the evidence, institutions, farms, schools, businesses, media, and policy tools our communities need to <em>repair, rise, and govern</em> their future.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-feat-col">
      <h3><span class="roman">III.</span>The Method</h3>
      <p class="drop">Operated by an <em>agentic-first staff</em> &mdash; AI agents under human direction &mdash; producing institutional-scale output from a deliberately lean operating team built to outlast cycles.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-letter">
  <div class="vc-letter-grid">
    <aside class="vc-letter-side reveal">
      <span class="vc-letter-rubric">Letter from the Founder</span>
      <h2 class="dept">A note to the lineage.</h2>
    </aside>
    <div class="vc-letter-body reveal">
      <h2>This is not a campaign. It is <em>a record being built.</em></h2>
      <p class="first">For three centuries the obligations of emancipation went unrecorded &mdash; not because they were unknown, but because the architecture of remedy was never built. E5 Enclave is the architecture. The Coalition is the network. The Five Pillars are the doctrine. The projects are the proof.</p>
      <p>We do not promise a finish line. We promise <em>discipline of scope</em> &mdash; naming precisely what we are doing, and what we are not. We promise coordination over competition. We promise that what is measured cannot be dismissed.</p>
      <p>The center holds. The work begins.</p>
      <div class="vc-letter-sign">
        <span class="signature">{{ site.founder.name }}</span>
        <span class="name-block">{{ site.founder.title }}<em>{{ site.fullName }}</em></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-values">
  <div class="vc-values-head reveal">
    <div class="lhs">
      <span class="rubric">The Doctrine — V Tenets</span>
      <h2>What E5 <em>is.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="rhs">
      Five institutional values. The center holds. Each tenet is published openly and audited against practice, in the manner of any standing institution worthy of its charter.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="vc-values-list reveal">
    <div class="vc-value-row">
      <span class="num">i.</span>
      <span class="name">Empirical Integrity</span>
      <span class="body">Decisions grounded in dual-source-verified evidence. What is measured cannot be dismissed.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-value-row">
      <span class="num">ii.</span>
      <span class="name">Sovereign Capacity</span>
      <span class="body">Communities own their data, their institutions, and their futures. We coordinate; we do not absorb.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-value-row">
      <span class="num">iii.</span>
      <span class="name">Black-First</span>
      <span class="body">Built by and for the lineage. Coalition allies strengthen the work. The center holds.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-value-row">
      <span class="num">iv.</span>
      <span class="name">Radical Transparency</span>
      <span class="body">Substantial research published openly. Operating model in plain language. Records made public.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-value-row">
      <span class="num">v.</span>
      <span class="name">Intergenerational Accountability</span>
      <span class="body">Built for the people who will inherit it. We are stewards, not owners.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-pillars" id="pillars">
  <div class="vc-pillars-orn vc-orn-rule reveal"><span class="mk">✦</span></div>
  <div class="vc-pillars-rubric reveal">The Five Pillars</div>
  <h2 class="vc-pillars-h reveal">The structure of the harm is the structure of the <em>remedy.</em></h2>
  <div class="vc-pillars-grid reveal">
    {% for pillar in pillars %}
    <a class="vc-pillar" href="/pillars/{{ pillar.slug }}/" aria-label="{{ pillar.name }} pillar">
      <div class="num">{{ pillar.numeral }}.</div>
      <div class="name">{{ pillar.name }}</div>
      <div class="body">{{ pillar.body }}</div>
      <div class="flag">{{ pillar.flagLabel }}<em>{{ pillar.flagName }}</em></div>
    </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-r246" id="restitution">
  <div class="vc-r246-grid">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="vc-r246-rubric">A Campaign under Emancipated</div>
      <h2 class="vc-r246-h">Restitution <em>246.</em></h2>
      <p class="vc-r246-deck">A disciplined wage-loss and opportunity-loss framework for the 246 years of stolen labor endured by the lineage under American chattel slavery &mdash; and the inherent loss of opportunity caused by that theft.</p>
      <p class="vc-r246-body">Restitution 246 does not claim to settle the full reparations question. It does not address pain and suffering, racial terror, family separation, land theft, cultural theft, or every harm that followed slavery. Those injuries require their own frameworks. This campaign is one disciplined lane &mdash; built on the five questions, anchored to the Craemer (2015) wage-hour methodology.</p>
      <div class="vc-r246-cta">
        <a href="/restitution-246/" class="vc-cta-primary">Read the Campaign <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
        <a href="/record/measure-the-wound/" class="vc-cta-link">See also: <em>Measure the Wound</em> &mdash; the foundational record of harms.</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside class="vc-mech reveal">
      <div class="label">The Working Mechanism</div>
      <div class="num">$120<span class="t">T</span></div>
      <div class="tag">Bond held in perpetuity.</div>
      <p class="body">Interest payments directed to the lineage as partial restitution for lost wages and inherited loss of opportunity. The principal remains held in perpetuity; the interest becomes the distributable mechanism.</p>
      <hr/>
      <dl class="attr">
        <div class="attr-row"><dt>Framework</dt><dd>Lloyd Kelly</dd></div>
        <div class="attr-row"><dt>Methodology</dt><dd>Craemer, 2015</dd></div>
        <div class="attr-row"><dt>Status</dt><dd>Open Record</dd></div>
      </dl>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-pull">
  <div class="vc-pull-inner reveal">
    <div class="vc-pull-orn vc-orn-rule"><span class="mk">§</span></div>
    <div class="vc-pull-rubric">From the Vision</div>
    <blockquote>A coordinated, sovereign lineage building <em>institutions built by and for the communities it harmed</em> &mdash; for the next thousand years.</blockquote>
    <div class="vc-pull-cite">{{ site.name }} · Founding Doctrine · MMXXVI</div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-record" id="record">
  <div class="vc-record-orn vc-orn-rule reveal"><span class="mk">¶</span></div>
  <div class="vc-record-rubric reveal">— The Record —</div>
  <h2 class="vc-record-h reveal">Dispatches from <em>the Coalition.</em></h2>
  <p class="vc-record-intro reveal">Three documents anchor the founding work — a Think Tank dispatch, the foundational record of the harms we repair, and the campaign framework for restitution. Each is published openly, audited against practice, and built to be cited.</p>
  <div class="vc-record-grid reveal">
    {% for paper in papers %}
    <article class="vc-record-card{% if paper.lead %} vc-record-lead{% endif %}">
      <div class="kind">{{ paper.kind }}</div>
      <h3 class="title">{{ paper.title }}</h3>
      <p class="lede">{{ paper.lede }}</p>
      <a href="/record/{{ paper.slug }}/" class="link">Read on E5 <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="vc-record-colophon">Set in Cormorant Garamond &amp; Inter. Convened in {{ site.established.city }}. <em>For the next thousand years.</em></p>
</section>

<section class="vc-contrib" id="coalition">
  <div class="vc-contrib-orn vc-orn-rule reveal"><span class="mk">¶</span></div>
  <div class="vc-contrib-rubric reveal">— Contributors to the Founding —</div>
  <h2 class="vc-contrib-h reveal">A masthead of <em>builders, stewards, and elders.</em></h2>
  <div class="vc-contrib-grid reveal">
    {% for col in contributors.columns %}
    <div class="vc-contrib-col">
      <h4>{{ col.title }}</h4>
      <ul>
        {% for m in col.members %}<li>{{ m.name }}<small>{{ m.role }}</small></li>{% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="vc-join" id="join">
  <div class="vc-join-rubric">How to join</div>
  <h2 class="vc-join-h">Apply to <em>the Coalition.</em></h2>
  <p class="vc-join-deck">Black-led organizations, individual builders, funders, and partner institutions: the Coalition is open. Submit your interest and a member of the Council will respond.</p>
  <div class="vc-join-cta">
    <a href="/coalition/apply/" class="vc-cta-primary">Apply <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    <a href="mailto:{{ site.contact.primary }}" class="vc-cta-link">or, <em>email the Council</em></a>
  </div>
</section>


